# Data API Storage Patterns

## Context
- All data storage uses the Busibox data-api service
- No direct database access (no Prisma, no SQL)
- Uses @jazzmind/busibox-app client functions
- Data is scoped per-user via token-based auth

## Requirements

### Data API Client

```typescript
// lib/data-api-client.ts
import {
  generateId,
  getNow,
  queryRecords,
  insertRecords,
  updateRecords,
  deleteRecords,
  ensureDocuments,
} from '@jazzmind/busibox-app';
import type { AppDataSchema } from '@jazzmind/busibox-app';
```

### Document Setup

Each data collection requires a document with a schema:

```typescript
export const DOCUMENTS = {
  ITEMS: 'my-app-items',
} as const;

export const itemSchema: AppDataSchema = {
  fields: {
    id: { type: 'string', required: true, hidden: true },
    name: { type: 'string', required: true, label: 'Name', order: 1 },
    // ... more fields
    createdAt: { type: 'string', readonly: true, hidden: true },
    updatedAt: { type: 'string', readonly: true, hidden: true },
  },
  displayName: 'Items',
  itemLabel: 'Item',
  sourceApp: 'my-app',
  visibility: 'authenticated',
  allowSharing: false,
  graphNode: '',
  graphRelationships: [],
};
```

### Ensure Documents Before CRUD

Documents use `visibility: 'authenticated'` so one container exists for all app users.
Per-record access control is handled at the record level (via `data_records` table RLS).

```typescript
export async function ensureDataDocuments(token: string) {
  return ensureDocuments(token, {
    items: { name: DOCUMENTS.ITEMS, schema: itemSchema, visibility: 'authenticated' },
  }, 'my-app');
}
```

### CRUD Operations

```typescript
// List
const result = await queryRecords<Item>(token, documentId, {
  orderBy: [{ field: 'createdAt', direction: 'desc' }],
  limit: 50,
});

// Get by ID
const result = await queryRecords<Item>(token, documentId, {
  where: { field: 'id', op: 'eq', value: itemId },
  limit: 1,
});

// Create
const item = { id: generateId(), ...input, createdAt: getNow(), updatedAt: getNow() };
await insertRecords(token, documentId, [item]);

// Update
await updateRecords(token, documentId, updates, { field: 'id', op: 'eq', value: itemId });

// Delete
await deleteRecords(token, documentId, { field: 'id', op: 'eq', value: itemId });
```

### API Route Pattern

```typescript
export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  const auth = await requireAuthWithTokenExchange(request, 'data-api');
  if (auth instanceof NextResponse) return auth;

  const documentIds = await ensureDataDocuments(auth.apiToken);
  const result = await listItems(auth.apiToken, documentIds.items);
  return NextResponse.json(result);
}
```

<critical>
- ALWAYS use requireAuthWithTokenExchange with 'data-api' audience
- ALWAYS call ensureDataDocuments before CRUD operations
- ALWAYS use generateId() and getNow() from @jazzmind/busibox-app
- NEVER access databases directly - all storage goes through data-api
</critical>
